<input type="hidden" name="course" value="problemset">
<input type="hidden" name="task" value="2205">
A Gray code is a list of all $2^n$ bit strings of length $n$, where any two successive strings differ in exactly one bit (i.e., their Hamming distance is one).<br />
<br />
Your task is to create a Gray code for a given length $n$.<br />
<br />
<b id="input">Input</b><br />
<br />
The only input line has an integer $n$.<br />
<br />
<b id="output">Output</b><br />
<br />
Print $2^n$ lines that describe the Gray code. You can print any valid solution.<br />
<br />
<b id="constraints">Constraints</b><br />
<ul>
<li>$1 \le n \le 16$<br />
</ul>
<b id="example">Example</b><br />
<br />
Input:<br />
<code>2</code><br />
<br />
Output:<br />
<code>00<br />
01<br />
11<br />
10</code>    </div>
